{
  "texts": [
    "With fermions, one should replace certain commutators by anticommutators where appropriate.",
    "Physical setups where asymptotic states carry nontrivial topology include anyons in three-dimensional Chern-Simons theories or dyons in four-dimensional U(1) gauge theories, see[12][13][14] and references therein.",
    "Note that some of the literature from the last century (see, e.g., refs.",
    "[21][22][23]) used a similar but slightly different notation, in which the blobs for iM were denoted with a \"+\" and the blobs for iM † were denoted with a \"-\" and had an overall minus sign.",
    "Our notation makes all factors as explicit as possible."
  ]
}